I'm currently focused on pinpointing the root cause of the error flagged on line 50 within `views/ExcelLabs.tsx`. The compiler is reporting an unused left-hand side of a comma operator within the expression `=LINEST(B2:B20, A2:A20^{1,2,3})`. I need to understand how this formula is intended to work and identify why the compiler is flagging it. My next step will be to dissect the formula to ensure the comma operator is used in the appropriate context.


**Interpreting the Formula Syntax**

I've realized the code snippet likely renders Excel formulas as text within `<code>` tags. The error stems from how JSX handles the comma operator within the expression `{1,2,3}` which is the power of a series of exponents. JSX interprets this as JavaScript. The compiler is complaining about unused values (1,2) of the comma operator, but the intent is likely to pass an array to the Excel formula in the `LINEST` function.


