I've determined the issue is JSX misinterpreting `{1,2,3}` as JavaScript, necessitating literal text rendering. The cleanest fix involves enclosing the entire formula within a string within the `<code>` tag, like this: `<code className="text-emerald-400">{"=LINEST(B2:B20, A2:A20^{1,2,3})"}</code>`. The lack of such brackets is why the existing code on lines such as `=MMULT(MINVERSE(A1:C3), D1:D3)` and `=A2*(1+$B$1)` render without issue. I'll need to check the remaining lines as well, to ensure the same logic is applied. I should also check compliance within `services/geminiService.ts`.


